How does the Erbium YAG laser work? 
The laser energy targets the water in your skin cells, vaporizing the cells to remove micro-layers of skin at a time. The device is also fractionated, creating micro-channels in the skin that trigger the body to generate new cells and produce more collagen. This leads to smoother, youthful skin with visible reduction in lines, scarring, and hyperpigmentation. 

What does fractional resurfacing treat? 
Facial lines and wrinkles
Scarring
Uneven pigment
Sun damage 
Birthmarks
Acne scarring”

And how the muscles are continuous in the SMAS helps #EMFACE give your face the lift that you’re looking for, without a scalpel or needle.

Now, while Emface may not be a substitute for a facelift, it can absolutely prolong your need for one, as we’ve seen in my patient’s before and afters. 

Emface is strengthening your very own tissue and taking anti-aging WAY beyond the surface.

Facial fat transfer, also referred to as facial fat grafting or fat injection, is a popular cosmetic procedure aimed at revitalizing the face by restoring lost volume and improving its overall appearance. The technique involves carefully transferring fat from one part of the body to the face, resulting in a more youthful and rejuvenated look.

The harvested fat undergoes a purification process to remove any impurities and damaged cells, leaving behind a concentrated and purified fat graft. This purified fat is then skillfully injected into specific areas of the face that require enhancement or volume restoration. Common target areas include the cheeks, nasolabial folds (smile lines), and under-eye hollows, where signs of aging and volume loss are more noticeable.

One of the significant advantages of facial fat transfer is its potential for more natural-looking and long-lasting results compared to traditional facial fillers. Since the patient’s own fat cells are used, there is a reduced risk of allergic reactions or adverse responses. Additionally, the transplanted fat integrates with the existing facial tissues, providing a smoother and more harmonious appearance.
